hwSIPMIB.description: The HUAWEI-SIP-MIB contains objects to Manage the SIP client configuration.

hwSIPID.name: hwSIPID
hwSIPID.description: The unique identification of a SIP gateway. By default, this object should have the value 'VRP-GATEWAY'.

hwSIPPasswordType.name: hwSIPPasswordType
hwSIPPasswordType.description: The display type of a SIP gateway password. By default, this object should have the value simple(1).

hwSIPPassword.name: hwSIPPassword
hwSIPPassword.description: a SIP gateway password. By default, this object should have the value 'VRP-SIP'.

hwSIPTransport.name: hwSIPTransport
hwSIPTransport.description: the transport type of SIP packets. By default, this object should have the value udp(1).

hwSIPSourceIP.name: hwSIPSourceIP
hwSIPSourceIP.description: The source IP address of the local peer acted as UA.

hwSIPCallDebugSwitch.name: hwSIPCallDebugSwitch
hwSIPCallDebugSwitch.description: Indicate whether the SIP calls debug information should be generated. By default, this object should have the value disabled(2).

hwSIPRegisterDebugSwitch.name: hwSIPRegisterDebugSwitch
hwSIPRegisterDebugSwitch.description: Indicate whether the SIP calls debug information should be generated. By default, this object should have the value disabled(2).

hwSIPTrapsControl.name: hwSIPTrapsControl
hwSIPTrapsControl.description: Indicates wether the SIP module is permitted to generate traps. By default, this object should have the value disabled(2).

hwSIPStatisticClear.name: hwSIPStatisticClear
hwSIPStatisticClear.description: The object is used to clear the statistic information of a SIP gateway. Note that it is significative only when this object is executed 'set' operation.
